Part I - (Ford GoBike System Data Exploration)¶

by (T.J.Adel Al-Dajani)¶

Introduction¶

This data set includes information about individual rides made in a bike-sharing system covering the greater San Francisco Bay area. The features included in the dataset : Trip Duration (seconds) , Start Time and Date , End Time and Date , Start Station ID , Start Station Name , Start Station Latitude , Start Station Longitude , End Station ID , End Station Name, End Station Latitude , End Station Longitude , Bike ID , User Type (Subscriber or Customer Subscriber = Member or Customer = Casual) , Member Year of Birth, Member Gender

df['start_time'] =  pd.to_datetime(df['start_time'])
df['start_date'] = df.start_time.dt.strftime('%Y-%m-%d')
df['hour_of_day'] = df.start_time.dt.strftime('%H')
df['day_of_week'] = df.start_time.dt.strftime('%A')
df['month'] = df.start_time.dt.strftime('%B')

Main feature(s) of interest in your dataset¶

Trip Duration , Start Time and Date , End Time and Date, User Type , Member Year of Birth , Member Gender

Features in the dataset that will help support our investigation into our feature(s) of interest¶

1) How long does the average trip take?

2) do most users have bike share for all trip?

3) Which gender used most ford bike?

4) what is the most common hour of the day that people ride bikes?

5) What are the most popular start and end stations?

6) Does the trip duration depend upon if a user is a subscriber or customer?

7) Does the trip duration depend upon gender?

8) What gender has the has the most subscribers?

9) Does member gender affect having bike share for all trip?

10) Is there a relationship between user type and hour of the day?

11) Does the trip duration depends on user type and gender?

12) What is the average trip duration every day for each gender?

Univariate Exploration¶

How long does the average trip take?

since duration is a quantitaive data a histogram will be used

In [16]:
bins = np.arange(0, df['duration_sec'].max() + 50, 50)
plt.hist(data = df, x = 'duration_sec', bins = bins);
plt.xlim(0,5000);
plt.xlabel('Ride Duration (sec)');
plt.xticks([0, 500, 1000, 1500, 2000, 2500, 3000, 3500, 4000, 4500]);
plt.ylabel('Number of Rides');
plt.title('Avg. ride duration');

as noted from the above plot most trips are small in distance so that the users reach their destination within 8 - 10 min (around 500 sec)

def myCountPlot (df, xVar, huevar, order=None,  palette=None) :
    '''
(their defaults are set)
docstring: IMPORTANT explain function here
inputs:
output:
'''
# set plot dimensions
    plt.figure (figsize=[14, 6])
# plot
    sb.countplot (data=df, x = xVar, hue=huevar, edgecolor='black' , order=order,palette=palette) ;
# OPTIONAL: AFTER plotting, clean up variable names
    xVar = xVar.replace("_", " ") 
# replace _ with a space
    huevar=huevar.replace("_", " ")
# Add title and format it
    plt.title(f''' Distribution of {xVar} by {huevar}'''.title(), fontsize = 14, weight = "bold" )
# Add x label and format it
    plt.xlabel (xVar.title( ), fontsize = 10, weight = "bold")
# Add y label and format it
    plt.ylabel ('Frequency'.title(), fontsize = 10, weight = "bold" )

What is the average trip duration every day for each gender?

In [32]:
plt.figure(figsize=(10,8))
day_order = ['Monday', 'Tuesday', 'Wednesday', 'Thursday', 'Friday', 'Saturday', 'Sunday']
sb.stripplot(x = "day_of_week", y = "duration_min", hue = 'member_gender', data = df, order = day_order, jitter = 0.35, dodge = True, palette = "Dark2");
plt.xlabel('Day of Week');
plt.ylabel('Avg. Trip Duration in Minute');
plt.yscale('log');
plt.yticks([1, 2, 5, 10, 20, 50, 100], [1, 2, 5, 10, 20, 50, 100]);
ax = plt.gca()
ax.set_yticklabels([],minor = True);
plt.title("Avg. trip duration on every day of week for each gender");

We can note that Males have the highest trip durations everday compared to Females and Others

Relationships observed in this part of the investigation¶

We can see from above that Males Have the highest trip durations everyday and in both User types

Conclusions¶

1) It is clear now that Males used Ford Bike the most.

2) The hours that Ford Bike is mostly used is at 8 am and 5 pm which is predicted since at these times people go to work and leave work.

3) It was discovered that the most common start station is Market St at 10th St. And the most common end station is San Francisco Caltrain Station 2 (Townsend St at 4th St)
